                <note rend="inline" type="source">374.115 Standard Oil Company/3: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Shoemaker</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sofia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-27T18:00:00+02:00"
                            >October 27, 1931—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 27—3:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>27. Contents of Department’s telegram No. 8, October 24, 1 p.m., communicated
                    this afternoon to the Prime Minister who was visibly moved by the force of the
                    message and who assured me with every mark of sincerity that steps will be taken
                    immediately to accord full satisfaction to the Standard Oil Company within the
                    limits of order No. 69.</p>
                <p>In cooperation with local director of the Standard Oil Company the Legation will
                    continue to follow the matter closely in an effort to see that effect is given
                    to this promise.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Shoemaker</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
